Van Drew Teams With Rio Grande Company to Donate Masks https://t.co/svANN7Pb3y via @heraldnews

Over the last few hours, storms and powerful winds have damaged huge areas of South Jersey, while we are in the midst of a public health crisis. I am asking the Governor to declare an immediate State of Emergency to help our community rebuild. We need the help now more than ever.
White House, Democrats near deal to replenish small business relief funds https://t.co/64pjiIsS2D

Our small businesses, those in healthcare, and the sick should be the only priority of legislation regarding Coronavirus.

DMOs help our economy thrive in South Jersey. We must include these groups in our legislation as they will help get our economy back to its feet when it is safe to be in public.
https://t.co/YHPg20fNTp

Congress and the agencies we oversee must ensure these precious funds go to help those in need, not corporations or institutions that already have access to money.
